---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-you-need', text: 'What You Need to Know', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'common-mistakes', text: 'Common Mistakes', level: 2 },
  { id: 'checklist', text: 'First-Timer Checklist', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Budget Insurance', href: '/best/budget-insurance' },
  { title: 'Short-Term Insurance', href: '/best/short-term-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'Understanding Coverage', href: '/guides/understanding-coverage' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'type', header: 'Type' },
  { key: 'ease', header: 'Ease of Use' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Monthly Cost' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'SafetyWing', type: 'Travel medical', ease: 'Very easy', price: '$45-85', bestFor: 'Testing expat life' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', type: 'Full health', ease: 'Moderate', price: '$200-500', bestFor: 'Committed move' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', type: 'Full health', ease: 'Moderate', price: '$100-250', bestFor: 'Budget full coverage' },
  { provider: 'World Nomads', type: 'Travel medical', ease: 'Very easy', price: '$80-200', bestFor: 'Adventure travel' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', type: 'Full health', ease: 'Moderate', price: '$150-400', bestFor: 'Europe-based' },
];

const mistakesColumns = [
  { key: 'mistake', header: 'Mistake' },
  { key: 'consequence', header: 'Consequence' },
  { key: 'solution', header: 'Solution' },
];

const mistakesRows = [
  { mistake: 'No insurance at all', consequence: 'One hospital visit can cost thousands', solution: 'Get at least travel medical insurance' },
  { mistake: 'Keeping home country insurance', consequence: 'May not cover you abroad', solution: 'Get international coverage' },
  { mistake: 'Choosing the cheapest option', consequence: 'Inadequate coverage when needed', solution: 'Balance cost with actual coverage' },
  { mistake: 'Not reading exclusions', consequence: 'Denied claims surprise you', solution: 'Read the policy document' },
  { mistake: 'Waiting to get insurance', consequence: 'Pre-existing conditions excluded', solution: 'Get coverage before you leave' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Insurance for First-Time Expats 2026"
  description="New to living abroad? Compare international health insurance options for first-time expats. Find easy-to-understand coverage that protects you without overwhelming complexity."
  headline="Best Insurance for First-Time Expats"
  subheadline="Moving abroad for the first time? International health insurance can be confusing. Here's a straightforward guide to getting the coverage you need."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-first-time-expat-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for First-Time Expats</h2>
  <p>
    These options work best for people new to expat life:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🎒</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Testing Expat Life</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Start at $45/month, cancel anytime. Perfect if you're not sure how long you'll stay abroad.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🏠</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Committed Move</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Full health insurance for long-term expats. Comprehensive coverage with excellent service.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💰</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Budget Full Coverage</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Full health insurance at lower prices. Good if you need real coverage but budget is tight.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌍</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Europe</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Strong European network, good service. Ideal if you're moving to Europe.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-you-need">What First-Time Expats Need to Know</h2>
  <p>
    International health insurance is different from what you're used to at home:
  </p>

  <h3>Two Main Types</h3>

  <h4>Travel Medical Insurance</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Covers emergencies and new conditions</li>
    <li>Does NOT cover pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Does NOT cover routine care</li>
    <li>Cheaper ($45-200/month)</li>
    <li>Easy to buy, cancel anytime</li>
    <li>Examples: SafetyWing, World Nomads</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Good for:</strong> Testing expat life, short-term stays, healthy people who mainly need emergency coverage.</p>

  <h4>Full Health Insurance</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Covers everything like "real" insurance</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions covered after waiting period</li>
    <li>Routine care, specialists, prescriptions included</li>
    <li>More expensive ($150-500+/month)</li>
    <li>Annual commitment typical</li>
    <li>Examples: Cigna, Bupa, Allianz, IMG</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Good for:</strong> Long-term expats, people with health conditions, families, those who want comprehensive coverage.</p>

  <h3>Your Home Insurance Probably Won't Work</h3>
  <p>
    Common misconceptions:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>US insurance:</strong> Almost never covers you abroad</li>
    <li><strong>UK NHS:</strong> Doesn't cover you outside the UK</li>
    <li><strong>Travel insurance from home:</strong> Usually limited to short trips</li>
    <li><strong>Credit card insurance:</strong> Very limited, short-term only</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You need international health insurance designed for living abroad.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="New to Expat Insurance?"
    description="Start with an easy option and upgrade as your needs become clearer."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">First-Timer Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>SafetyWing — Best for Testing Expat Life</h3>
  <p>
    If you're not sure how long you'll stay abroad, SafetyWing is the easiest place to start.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Why it works for first-timers:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Sign up in 5 minutes online</li>
    <li>No health questions</li>
    <li>Monthly billing—cancel anytime</li>
    <li>Only $45-85/month</li>
    <li>Covers 180+ countries</li>
    <li>Simple, easy to understand</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Limitations to understand:</strong> This is travel medical insurance. Pre-existing conditions aren't covered. No routine care. If you have ongoing health needs, this isn't enough.</p>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Healthy first-time expats testing the waters.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/safetywing">Read our full SafetyWing review</a></p>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best for Committed Move</h3>
  <p>
    If you're making a real move abroad, Cigna Global provides comprehensive coverage.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Why it works for first-timers:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Real health insurance, not just travel medical</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions covered after waiting period</li>
    <li>Excellent customer service</li>
    <li>Large global network</li>
    <li>Multiple plan levels to choose from</li>
    <li>Telemedicine included</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> More expensive. Annual commitment. Requires health questions. Worth it for long-term moves.</p>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> First-timers making a committed move who want real coverage.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>IMG Global — Best Budget Full Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    If you want full health insurance but budget is a concern, IMG offers good value.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Why it works for first-timers:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Full health insurance at lower prices</li>
    <li>High deductible options to reduce cost</li>
    <li>Pre-existing covered after waiting period</li>
    <li>Multiple plan options</li>
    <li>Good catastrophic coverage</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Service not as polished as Cigna/Bupa. Network smaller. Claims may be slower. Good value for the price.</p>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious first-timers who need real coverage.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/img-global">Read our full IMG Global review</a></p>

  <h2 id="common-mistakes">Common First-Timer Mistakes</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mistakesColumns} rows={mistakesRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Mistake: Assuming You're Covered</h3>
  <p>
    Many first-time expats assume their existing insurance covers them abroad. It usually doesn't. Check your policy—most home country insurance explicitly excludes coverage outside the country, or limits it to short trips.
  </p>

  <h3>Mistake: Going Uninsured</h3>
  <p>
    "I'm young and healthy, I don't need insurance." One broken bone, one appendicitis, one accident can cost $10,000-50,000+. Even in countries with affordable healthcare, serious emergencies are expensive.
  </p>

  <h3>Mistake: Waiting Until Something Happens</h3>
  <p>
    Once you have a health issue, it becomes a "pre-existing condition" that may be excluded or have waiting periods. Get insurance BEFORE you need it.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Don't Make These Mistakes"
    description="Get covered before you leave. It's easier and cheaper."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="checklist">First-Timer Checklist</h2>

  <h3>Before You Leave</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>☐ Get international health insurance (at minimum, travel medical)</li>
    <li>☐ Save policy documents accessible offline</li>
    <li>☐ Save emergency phone numbers</li>
    <li>☐ Understand what's covered and what's not</li>
    <li>☐ Get any needed vaccinations (often covered)</li>
    <li>☐ Refill prescriptions for transition period</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Choosing Your Insurance</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>☐ Decide: travel medical vs full health insurance</li>
    <li>☐ Check if your destination has specific requirements</li>
    <li>☐ Compare 2-3 options</li>
    <li>☐ Read what's excluded, not just what's covered</li>
    <li>☐ Check the claims process</li>
    <li>☐ Verify your destination is covered</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>After Arriving</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>☐ Find nearby hospitals/clinics in your network</li>
    <li>☐ Understand how to use your insurance locally</li>
    <li>☐ Know: direct billing vs reimbursement</li>
    <li>☐ Consider upgrading if you decide to stay long-term</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>I'm only going for a few months—do I need insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. Even a short trip can result in expensive medical bills. At minimum, get travel medical insurance like SafetyWing ($45/month). It's cheap insurance against potentially devastating costs.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I start with travel medical and upgrade later?</h3>
  <p>
    This is a reasonable approach. Start with SafetyWing to test expat life, then upgrade to full health insurance if you decide to stay. Just be aware that any conditions you develop become "pre-existing" for the new policy.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I have a pre-existing condition?</h3>
  <p>
    Travel medical insurance won't cover it. Full health insurance will cover it after a waiting period (typically 12-24 months). If you have ongoing health needs, start with full insurance sooner rather than later.
  </p>

  <h3>How much should I spend on insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    Budget at least $50-100/month for basic coverage. For comprehensive full health insurance, expect $200-400/month. Don't go uninsured to save $50/month—one emergency can cost more than years of premiums.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use my insurance in multiple countries?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, international health insurance is designed for this. Check your "area of coverage"—most plans cover worldwide except US (cheapest), or worldwide including US (more expensive). Within your area, you can travel freely.
  </p>

  <h3>What's the easiest option to start with?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing. Sign up online in 5 minutes, no health questions, starts immediately, cancel anytime. It's not comprehensive, but it's the easiest entry point for first-time expats.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Coverage options and requirements vary. We are not insurance brokers. Always verify coverage details directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
